&lt;strong&gt;Skills:&lt;/strong&gt; Process Flow Diagrams (PFD), Logic Diagrams, and other engineering documentation. Computational Fluid Dynamics (CFD) modeling experience is preferred but not required. CAD experience preferred but not required. Ability to read, analyze and interpret technical data and information. Strong computer skills. Ability to write reports, business correspondence, and procedure manuals. Presents information and responds to questions from peers, clients, senior management, regulators and external engineering professionals and vendors. Travel Requirements: Travel (up to 15%) and may involve extended periods of one week in the field and/or international travel. Occasional work in industrial environments for short periods of time in support of field data gathering, troubleshooting, and new process implementation.&lt;br&gt;
